 a more thorough understanding of the culture of printing and reading, of the political function of invectives, and of the general role of dissensus in early modern French society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aBooks and readingxHistoryx16th centuryxFrance. 0aBooks and readingzFrancexHistoryy16th century. 0aFrench literaturexHistory and criticismx16th century. 0aFrench literaturey16th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aInvective in literaturexFrankreichxFrance. 0aInvective in literature. 0aPolitical satire, FrenchxHistory and criticism. 0aReligious satire, FrenchxHistory and criticism. 0aScandals in literature. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 16th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804773546zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804773546423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804773546.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles